<subSubSection id="3796656070DBFF3DFF23EE8A8BA5FE6E" pageId="165" pageNumber="166" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="7F3336EB70DBFF3DFF23EE8A8BA5FE6E" blockId="165.[151,1436,151,428]" pageId="165" pageNumber="166">
<emphasis id="4DF8EAF970DBFF3DFF23EE8A8B44FF3D" bold="true" box="[199,335,223,248]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="165" pageNumber="166" reason="1">Comments.</emphasis>
<typeStatus id="A037884970DBFF3DFEB3EEB58B85FF3D" box="[343,398,224,248]" pageId="165" pageNumber="166">Type</typeStatus>
material of this taxon could not be located during this study. However, the figure provided by 
<bibRefCitation id="1B1D4B1A70DBFF3DFF5BEF518B52FED9" author="Emery, C." box="[191,345,260,284]" pageId="165" pageNumber="166" pagination="241 - 256" refId="ref110715" refString="Emery, C. (1887) Catalogo delle formiche esistenti nelle collezioni del Museo Civico di Genova. Parte terza. Formiche della regione Indo-Malese e dell'Australia. Annali del Museo Civico di Storia Naturale Giacomo Doria (Genova), 24, 241 - 256." type="journal article" year="1887">Emery (1887</bibRefCitation>
, fig. 26) matches specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="B88C4D6870DBFF3DFD3DEF51899CFED9" authorityName="Heterick &amp; Shattuck" authorityYear="2011" baseAuthorityName="Heterick &amp; Shattuck" baseAuthorityYear="2011" box="[729,919,260,284]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Anonychomyrma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="165" pageNumber="166" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="4DF8EAF970DBFF3DFD3DEF51899CFED9" box="[729,919,260,284]" italics="true" pageId="165" pageNumber="166">Anonychomyrma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
held in ANIC and is unlike species of 
<taxonomicName id="B88C4D6870DBFF3DFA92EF508B07FE85" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Iridomyrmex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="165" pageNumber="166" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="4DF8EAF970DBFF3DFA92EF508B07FE85" italics="true" pageId="165" pageNumber="166">Iridomyrmex</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
known from the vicinity of this species’ 
<typeStatus id="A037884970DBFF3DFD33EF7D890CFE85" box="[727,775,296,320]" pageId="165" pageNumber="166">type</typeStatus>
locality. In this species the pronotum is relatively high and is set off from the mesonotum by an angle, and the propodeum is high and dome-like. This configuration differs from known Indonesian species of 
<taxonomicName id="B88C4D6870DBFF3DFDC2EF2588BCFE4D" box="[550,695,368,392]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Iridomyrmex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="165" pageNumber="166" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="4DF8EAF970DBFF3DFDC2EF2588BCFE4D" box="[550,695,368,392]" italics="true" pageId="165" pageNumber="166">Iridomyrmex</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Therefore, this name is treated as belonging to 
<taxonomicName id="B88C4D6870DBFF3DFB3AEF258F97FE4D" authorityName="Heterick &amp; Shattuck" authorityYear="2011" baseAuthorityName="Heterick &amp; Shattuck" baseAuthorityYear="2011" box="[1246,1436,368,392]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Anonychomyrma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="165" pageNumber="166" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="4DF8EAF970DBFF3DFB3AEF258F97FE4D" box="[1246,1436,368,392]" italics="true" pageId="165" pageNumber="166">Anonychomyrma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
rather than 
<taxonomicName id="B88C4D6870DBFF3DFEF2EFC18BACFE69" box="[278,423,404,428]" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Iridomyrmex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="165" pageNumber="166" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="4DF8EAF970DBFF3DFEF2EFC18BACFE69" box="[278,423,404,428]" italics="true" pageId="165" pageNumber="166">Iridomyrmex</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
